    <segment id="1" parent="8" relname="span">I&apos;d like to second Shapiro on the utility of presenting STS to the
general public, and in that vein ask if anyone else has looked at the
recent issue of DISCOVER on race. </segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="1" relname="elaboration"> It has several articles that look
at the construction of the concept and categories of race and how
these are justified and deployed in various contexts, including
&quot;science&quot;. </segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="4" relname="solutionhood"> Does ayone recognize any of the authors as regular participants in
STS enterprises? </segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="6" relname="span"> If not, why aren&apos;t the editors turning our way when
asking for commentary? </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="7" relname="span"> Perhaps SSSS could put together a resource
list of researchers and their interests to forward to the various
popular science and the public policy journals.</segment>
